{"title_page": "2019 Harvard Crimson football team", "text_new": "{{short description|American college football season}}\n{{Infobox college sports team season\n| mode = football\n| year = 2019\n| team = Harvard Crimson\n| image = Harvard Crimson.svg\n| image_size = 100\n| conference = Ivy League\n| short_conf = Ivy\n| record = 4\u20136\n| conf_record = 2\u20135\n| head_coach = [[Tim Murphy (American football coach)|Tim Murphy]]\n| hc_year = 26th\n| off_coach = Joel Lamb\n| oc_year = 14th\n| off_scheme = \n| def_coach = Scott Larkee\n| dc_year = 11th\n| def_scheme = \n| stadium = [[Harvard Stadium]]<br>(Capacity: 30,323)\n}}\n{{2019 Ivy League football standings}}\n[[File:Cornell vs. Harvard football Oct 12, 2019.jpg|thumb|The Crimson defeated Cornell, 35-22]]\nThe '''2019 Harvard Crimson football team''' represented [[Harvard University]] during the [[2019 NCAA Division I FCS football season]] as a member of the [[Ivy League]]. They were led by 26th-year head coach [[Tim Murphy (American football coach)|Tim Murphy]] and played their home games at [[Harvard Stadium]]. They finished the season 4\u20136 overall and 2\u20135 in Ivy League play to tie for sixth place.\n\n==Previous season==\nThe Crimson finished the [[2018 Harvard Crimson football team|2018 season]] 6\u20134, 4\u20133 in Ivy League play to finish in third place.\n\n==Preseason==\n===Preseason media poll===\nThe Ivy League released their preseason media poll on August 8, 2019. The Crimson were picked to finish in fourth place.<ref>{{cite web |title=Yale Named League Favorite in 2019 Football Preseason Poll |url=https://ivyleague.com/news/2019/8/8/yale-named-league-favorite-in-2019-football-preseason-poll.aspx |website=ivyleague.com |accessdate=August 8, 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Harvard Crimson|Predicted finish|Team|Votes (1st place)}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 1 || Yale || 119 (9)\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 2 || Dartmouth || 111 (2)\n|-